{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DeexpCdbg1WuotpDMed4uz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All pods are healthy. Here's a summary of what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** Two permission gaps in RabbitMQ:\n1. `app-user` had no permissions on `/app` — only `admin` and (incorrectly) `ops-user` did.\n2. `ops-user` had no permissions on `/ops` — only `admin` did.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n1. `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — gave `app-user` full configure/write/read on `/app`.\n2. `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — gave `ops-user` full configure/write/read on `/ops`.\n3. Deleted the stale `app-queue` that had an `x-queue-mode=lazy` property mismatch (it had been left over from a previous declaration), allowing `app-client` to redeclare it cleanly.\n\nAll 3 RabbitMQ nodes are running, both `app-client` and `ops-client` are `1/1 Running`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":340,"cache_read_input_tokens":32298,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":340},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8eeefc8-c30a-4e9d-b355-a5744d79cdb2","uuid":"63c7df28-5bca-4e9e-a151-6918c0025f9d","request_id":"req_011Cc5LJK6b3EWb58teeaGf6"}
